<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-4xl">
  <div class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none">
    <p class="mb-4 text-base-content/60">Last updated: June 1, 2023</p>

    <div class="alert bg-base-200 border-l-4 border-secondary/60 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-secondary" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 11c0-1.104.896-2 2-2s2 .896 2 2-.896 2-2 2-2-.896-2-2zm0 0V7m0 8v-2m0 0c-4.418 0-8 1.79-8 4v2h16v-2c0-2.21-3.582-4-8-4z" />
      </svg>
      <span>We prioritize the security of our users and their data. This policy outlines our commitment to protection.</span>
    </div>

    <div class="divider my-8 before:bg-secondary/20 after:bg-secondary/20">Our Security Practices</div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3">Data Protection</h3>
    <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">TLS/SSL</span> All data is encrypted in transit using TLS/SSL protocols</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">Encryption</span> Sensitive user data is encrypted at rest</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">Audits</span> Regular security audits and vulnerability assessments</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">Access Control</span> Access to user data is strictly limited and controlled</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3">Authentication and Authorization</h3>
    <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">Passwords</span> Secure password policies</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">MFA</span> Multi-factor authentication available</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">RBAC</span> Role-based access control</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3">Infrastructure Security</h3>
    <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">Patching</span> Servers and infrastructure regularly updated</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">Firewalls</span> Network security measures including firewalls and intrusion detection</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">Backups</span> Regular backups to prevent data loss</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="divider my-8 before:bg-secondary/20 after:bg-secondary/20">Vulnerability Reporting</div>
    <p class="mb-4">We value the input of security researchers and the broader community in identifying potential vulnerabilities. If you believe you've found a security vulnerability in our systems, we encourage you to report it to us.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3">How to Report</h3>
    <p class="mb-4">Please send detailed information about potential security issues to:</p>
    <p class="mb-6 font-mono text-secondary"><a href="mailto:security@genderbase.org" class="text-secondary hover:underline">security@genderbase.org</a></p>

    <p class="mb-4">Include the following in your report:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-8">
      <li class="mb-2">Description of the potential vulnerability</li>
      <li class="mb-2">Steps to reproduce the issue</li>
      <li class="mb-2">Any potential impact of the vulnerability</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3">Responsible Disclosure</h3>
    <p class="mb-4">We are committed to:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-8">
      <li class="mb-2">Acknowledging receipt of your vulnerability report within 48 hours</li>
      <li class="mb-2">Providing an estimated timeline for addressing the vulnerability</li>
      <li class="mb-2">Notifying you when the vulnerability is fixed</li>
      <li class="mb-2">Recognizing your contribution (if desired) once the vulnerability is addressed</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="divider my-8 before:bg-secondary/20 after:bg-secondary/20">User Responsibilities</div>
    <p class="mb-4">While we work hard to ensure the security of our platform, security is a shared responsibility. We encourage users to:</p>
    <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">Passwords</span> Use strong, unique passwords for your Genderbase account</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">MFA</span> Enable multi-factor authentication when available</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">Confidentiality</span> Keep your login credentials confidential</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">Sign Out</span> Sign out from your account when using shared devices</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-secondary badge-outline mt-1">Report</span> Report any suspicious activities related to your account</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="divider my-8 before:bg-secondary/20 after:bg-secondary/20">Security Updates</div>
    <p class="mb-8">We continually update our security measures to address new threats and vulnerabilities. This security policy may be updated periodically to reflect these changes.</p>

    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center mt-10">
      <a href="/privacy" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg shadow">Privacy Policy</a>
      <a href="/about" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg shadow">About Genderbase</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>